Package edu.udel.trnka.pta

Interface Summary
LabeledBracketingParser LabeledBracketingParser is analogous to SAXParser; an implementation provides methods to implement the events generated during parsing.
 

Class Summary
ComparedParseTree The same as the normal parse tree, but shows comparison to other parse trees
ComparedParseTreeSet  
ComparedParseTreeSetLabeledBracketingParser loads a ComparedParseTreeSet from a file, using labeled bracketing.
CondensedLexicalAmbiguitySelector LexicalAmbiguitySelector allows a user to visually select the preterminals for a given string.
ConstituentLabelDrawing ConstituentLabelDrawing represents the drawing of a node in a parse tree.
LabeledBracketingParserMachine LabeledBracketingParserMachine works somewhat like the SAXParserFactory class, in that it controls parsing of labeled bracketing by calling the appropriate methods of the specified LabeledBracketingParser.
LASWindow Note to self: LASWindow is unable to properly call pack() on itself; it must be added to a JDesktopPane first.
ParseTree Represents a single parse tree.
ParseTreeApplication Main application class.
ParseTreeLabeledBracketingParser The ParseTreeLabeledBracketingParser class can load a parse tree as represented using labeled bracketing.
ParseTreePanel The visualization of a parse tree in a JPanel.
ParseTreeSet  
ParseTreeSetLabeledBracketingParser Loads a ComparedParseTreeSet from a file using labeled bracketing.
ParseTreeWindow Window wrapper around ParseTreePanel
SentenceParses A list of parses for a given string.
StringInputStream Reads an input stream (binary data) from a string (character data).
